Steps to do mesh processing
1)set directory to be current folder
2)Generate cubit mesh model (with split fault), for example in this case open mesh file Curving_Strike_slip_fault_split.cub5 in Cubit
3)Open Journal Editor in Cubit, turn to Python mode (Translate to python)
4)Paste the python commands shown in python_cubit_output_v2.py to the Journal Editor
5)Press Play button, the output files will be listed in MESH folder
Output:
1) fault_file_id.dat:
  slave node#, node area, normal vector Vx, Vy, Vz, master node#   
2) mesh_file:
  element#, node1#,node2#,node3#,node4#,node5#,node6#,node7#,node8#
3) node_file:
  node#, x_coordinate, y_coordinate, z_coordinate
